 'bs.bodyfx.faq.title': 'Frequently Asked Questions',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.1.q': 'Does Body FX hurt?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.1.a': 'No. Most patients describe it as a warm massage with a gentle pulling/suction sensation. The high-voltage pulse phases produce a brief, snap-like sensation but are very tolerable. No anesthesia is required.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.sess.q': 'How long is each session?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.sess.a': 'From 30 to 60 minutes, according to the area treated and how many zones you do in one visit.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.2.q': 'How many sessions do I need?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.2.a': 'A typical course is 6–8 sessions, performed once a week. Some patients see early changes after 3–4 sessions; final results usually take the full course plus another 4–6 weeks for collagen rebuilding.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.3.q': 'Is there any downtime?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.3.a': 'No. You can return to work, exercise, or any normal activity immediately. No side effects, no downtime — slight redness in the treated area may last an hour or two, then fades on its own.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.4.q': 'Is Body FX a weight loss treatment?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.4.a': 'No. Body FX is a contouring treatment — it reduces fat thickness in treated areas and tightens skin, but it doesn\'t treat overall body weight. The best candidates are within a reasonable range of their target weight.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.5.q': 'Will Body FX help with cellulite?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.5.a': 'Yes — Body FX delivers measurable improvement in cellulite appearance over a series of sessions. For severe cellulite cases, EMTONE may be a more focused choice; combining the two often produces the strongest result.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.6.q': 'Is Body FX safe for darker skin tones?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.6.a': 'Yes. Body FX uses radiofrequency, which doesn\'t target melanin — making it completely safe across all Fitzpatrick skin types, with no pigmentation risk.',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.7.q': 'Can I do Body FX after a liposuction or BodyTite procedure?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.7.a': 'Yes — Body FX is excellent as a maintenance treatment after liposuction, BodyTite, or a tummy tuck. Your doctor will advise you on the right waiting period before starting (usually 4–6 weeks).',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.8.q': 'How is Body FX different from generic RF body sculpting?',
 'bs.bodyfx.faq.8.a': 'Body FX is an InMode-engineered device with ACE temperature feedback technology and combined RF + vacuum + high-voltage pulse delivery in one device. Generic \'RF body machines\' typically lack one or more of these components, the temperature control, or the clinical safety data. Hollywood Clinic uses only the authentic device.',
