 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.1': 'Consultation & assessment — your doctor evaluates your fat pockets, skin laxity, and cellulite, maps the target areas, and sets the right protocol and number of sessions.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.2': 'Cleansing & prep — the area is cleansed and a thin layer of glide gel is applied so the applicator moves smoothly and the energy is delivered evenly.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.3': 'Positioning — you lie down comfortably and the Body FX applicator is placed on the first target zone (abdomen, flanks, thighs, arms, or buttocks).',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.4': 'Combined energy — the device delivers radiofrequency heat, vacuum suction, and high-voltage pulses together, while ACE temperature feedback keeps the skin at the ideal therapeutic temperature.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.5': 'What you feel — a warm, deep suction-massage sensation with brief snap-like pulses. Comfortable and tolerable for most people, with no anesthesia needed.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.6': 'Even coverage — the applicator is moved in steady, overlapping passes so the whole area is treated uniformly.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.7': 'Finishing — the gel is removed and soothing skincare is applied. Slight redness may appear for an hour or two but is not visible to others.',
 'bs.bodyfx.pstep.8': 'Aftercare & plan — you return to work, exercise, or daily life immediately. A typical course is 6–8 sessions, once a week, with results building over the following weeks as collagen rebuilds.',
