 'sub.botox.video.title': 'Watch How Botox Works',
 'sub.botox.video.note': 'A quick look at a real Botox session at Hollywood Clinic.',
 'sub.botox.about.short': 'Botox is a purified protein injection that softens the muscles behind dynamic wrinkles — the forehead lines, frown lines, and crow\'s feet that deepen with expression. One of the most studied treatments in aesthetics, at Hollywood Clinic it\'s placed by certified injectors after a full facial assessment, for a refreshed, natural result that never looks frozen.',
 'sub.botox.acc.what': 'What is Botox?',
 'sub.botox.intro.compare': 'Botox vs. Other Treatments',
 'sub.botox.contra.intro': 'Botox is not suitable in the following cases. A full medical assessment is always done before treatment at Hollywood Clinic.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.1': 'Consultation & facial assessment — your injector studies your expressions and anatomy, listens to your goals, and plans the exact muscles and dosing for a natural result.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.2': 'Cleansing & mapping — the skin is cleansed and the precise injection points are marked while you make natural expressions.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.3': 'Comfort — the needle is extremely fine; numbing cream or ice can be used, though most people find it very tolerable.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.4': 'Injection — tiny amounts of Botox are placed into the targeted muscles with a fine needle. The session usually takes 10–15 minutes.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.5': 'What you feel — quick, light pinches at each point. No anesthesia needed and you can talk normally throughout.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.6': 'Right after — you return to your day immediately. Tiny bumps at the points settle within 15–30 minutes.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.7': 'Aftercare — stay upright for a few hours and avoid rubbing the area, heavy exercise, and saunas for 24 hours.',
 'sub.botox.pstep.8': 'Results & plan — softening begins in 3–5 days and is full by about two weeks, lasting 3–4 months. A quick review fine-tunes your next session.',
