 'sub.bodyfiller.ba.cap1': 'Skin smoothing & tone',
 'sub.bodyfiller.ba.cap2': 'Non-surgical buttock shaping',
 'sub.bodyfiller.gallery.title': 'Body Fillers Gallery',
 'sub.bodyfiller.gallery.eyebrow': 'Body Fillers in Action',
 'sub.bodyfiller.gallery.sub': 'A closer look at body filler shaping for the hips, buttocks, calves, and hands.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.doctors.eyebrow': 'Recommended Doctors',
 'sub.bodyfiller.doctors.title': 'Your Body Filler Specialists',
 'sub.bodyfiller.doc.view': 'View profile',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.eyebrow': 'Questions',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.title': 'Frequently Asked Questions',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.1.q': 'Are body fillers a real alternative to a BBL?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.1.a': 'Yes — for moderate shaping. Body fillers add volume and improve the shape of the buttocks and hips without surgery, fat transfer, or implants. They are ideal for filling hip dips and adding a natural lift. For very large-volume reshaping, a surgical BBL may still be needed, and we will tell you honestly which is right for you.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.2.q': 'How long do body fillers last?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.2.a': 'body filler typically lasts 12 to 18 months, depending on the area, the volume used, and your metabolism. The result fades gradually, and top-up sessions maintain it.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.3.q': 'How long is the session and is there downtime?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.3.a': 'A session takes 45 to 90 minutes according to the area and the volume used. Downtime is minimal — you may have some swelling, tenderness, or bruising for a few days. For buttock treatment we advise avoiding prolonged direct pressure (long sitting) for a short period, which we explain in your aftercare.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.4.q': 'Is it painful?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.4.a': 'We use topical and, where needed, local anaesthetic, and a blunt cannula rather than a sharp needle, so most women find it very tolerable. You may feel pressure as the filler is placed.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.5.q': 'Is it safe? Can it be reversed?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.5.a': 'When performed by a trained injector using genuine HA body filler, it is very safe. Because it is body-filler gel, it can be dissolved with hyaluronidase if ever needed — a key safety advantage over permanent options and unbranded fillers.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.6.q': 'How much does body filler cost?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.6.a': 'Body filler is priced by the millilitre, and larger body areas need more volume than facial filler, so the total depends on the area and how much shape you want. We give you a clear, itemised quote at your consultation — with genuine body filler only.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.7.q': 'Will it look or feel natural?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.7.a': 'Yes. body filler is designed to integrate with your own tissue, so the result feels natural to the touch and moves naturally. Our injectors shape and mould the filler for a smooth, symmetrical contour.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.8.q': 'Can body fillers rejuvenate the hands?',
 'sub.bodyfiller.faq.8.a': 'Yes. Ageing hands lose volume, which makes veins and tendons stand out. A small amount of body filler restores a smooth, youthful back-of-hand — one of the most natural and satisfying body-filler treatments.',
 'sub.bodyfiller.reviews.eyebrow': 'Client Reviews',
