    'sub.sculptra.video.note': "A quick look at a real Sculptra session at Hollywood Clinic.",
    'sub.sculptra.about.title': "What is Sculptra",
    'sub.sculptra.about.short': "Sculptra is an FDA-approved poly-L-lactic acid (PLLA) collagen biostimulator that gradually rebuilds your own collagen to restore facial volume, firmness and a natural lift — results that develop over months and can last up to two years.",
    'sub.sculptra.about.body': "Sculptra is a collagen biostimulator made from poly-L-lactic acid (PLLA), a biocompatible material used in medicine for decades. Unlike traditional fillers that add instant volume, Sculptra works with your body: once injected, the PLLA micro-particles gently stimulate your fibroblasts to produce new collagen, gradually restoring the deep structural support that thins with age. The result is a subtle, natural-looking improvement in facial volume, contour and firmness — not a filled or overdone look. Because it rebuilds your own collagen, results appear gradually over 6–12 weeks and can last up to two years. A typical course is 2–3 sessions spaced weeks apart. At Hollywood Clinic, Sculptra is reconstituted correctly, given time to hydrate, and injected with proper technique by trained doctors — the details that make Sculptra safe, even and long-lasting.",
    'sub.sculptra.ba.cap1': "Restored mid-face volume",
    'sub.sculptra.ba.cap2': "Firmer, lifted contour",
