 'laser.about.title': 'What Is Laser Hair Removal?',
 'laser.benefits.title': 'Benefits',
 'laser.about.body': 'Laser hair removal at Hollywood Clinic uses the Triton laser by InMode — an advanced platform that combines three laser wavelengths with powerful built-in cooling to remove unwanted hair safely and effectively on all skin types and tones, including darker and tanned skin. The laser targets the melanin pigment in the hair follicle, heating and disabling it so that hair regrows finer and sparser until it stops. Because Triton blends Alexandrite (755nm), Diode (810nm), and Nd:YAG (1064nm) wavelengths, treatments are fast, effective across different hair and skin types, and comfortable thanks to integrated cooling. Triton also performs skin laser treatments — gentle resurfacing for smoother skin. A course of sessions delivers long-lasting, smooth, hair-free skin with no downtime.',
 'laser.benefit.1': 'Long-lasting hair reduction — hair regrows finer and sparser until it stops',
 'laser.benefit.2': 'Safe and effective on all skin types and tones, including darker and tanned skin',
 'laser.benefit.3': 'Three laser wavelengths in one device for different hair and skin types',
 'laser.benefit.4': 'Powerful built-in cooling for a comfortable, well-tolerated treatment',
 'laser.benefit.5': 'Fast sessions — small areas take minutes, large areas are efficient',
 'laser.benefit.6': 'No downtime — return to daily activities immediately',
 'laser.benefit.7': 'Treats the face, underarms, arms, legs, bikini line, back, and full body',
 'laser.benefit.8': 'Reduces ingrown hairs and irritation from shaving and waxing',
 'laser.benefit.9': 'Also performs skin resurfacing for smoother skin',
 'laser.benefit.10': 'Smooth, hair-free skin that saves time and money long-term',
 'laser.who.1': 'Anyone wanting long-lasting reduction of unwanted hair',
 'laser.who.2': 'Women tired of shaving, waxing, or threading',
 'laser.who.3': 'People with ingrown hairs or irritation from other hair-removal methods',
 'laser.who.4': 'All skin tones — including darker and tanned skin, thanks to the Nd:YAG wavelength',
 'laser.who.5': 'Those treating small areas (upper lip, chin, underarms) or large areas (legs, back, full body)',
 'laser.who.6': 'People with hormonal or coarse hair seeking a more permanent solution',
 'laser.who.7': 'Anyone wanting smoother skin and freedom from daily hair removal',
 'laser.who.8': 'Adults in good health, after a quick skin assessment and patch test',
 'laser.contra.1': 'Pregnancy (treatment is usually postponed)',
 'laser.contra.2': 'Recent sun exposure, tanning, or self-tanner on the area (a waiting period is needed)',
 'laser.contra.3': 'Active infection, cold sores, or open wounds in the treatment area',
 'laser.contra.4': 'Recent use of isotretinoin (Roaccutane) — a waiting period is required',
 'laser.contra.5': 'Photosensitising medications or conditions — requires medical review',
 'laser.contra.6': 'History of keloid or abnormal scarring (assessed individually)',
 'laser.contra.7': 'Light, grey, white, or red hair with little pigment responds poorly to laser',
 'laser.contra.8': 'Recent chemical peels or aggressive treatments on the area',
 'laser.contra.9': 'Certain skin conditions or recent tattoos in the treatment zone',
 'laser.contra.10': 'A skin assessment and patch test are always done before laser at Hollywood Clinic',
 'laser.tech.1': 'Powered by Triton by InMode — an advanced multi-wavelength laser hair-removal platform',
 'laser.tech.2': 'Combines three wavelengths — Alexandrite (755nm), Diode (810nm), and Nd:YAG (1064nm) — for different hair and skin types',
 'laser.tech.3': 'The Nd:YAG wavelength makes treatment safe and effective on darker and tanned skin',
 'laser.tech.4': 'Powerful built-in contact cooling protects the skin and keeps treatment comfortable',
 'laser.tech.5': 'Can deliver multiple wavelengths for fast, thorough coverage',
 'laser.tech.6': 'Hollywood Clinic uses the authentic Triton device, operated by trained laser specialists',
 'laser.compare.1.label': 'Laser vs. Shaving & Waxing',
 'laser.compare.1.text': 'Shaving and waxing are temporary and cause regrowth, ingrowns, and irritation. Laser reduces hair long-term, so it regrows finer and sparser until it stops.',
 'laser.compare.2.label': 'Laser vs. IPL',
 'laser.compare.2.text': 'IPL uses scattered light and is generally weaker and less precise. A medical laser like Triton delivers focused, effective energy with better results in fewer sessions.',
 'laser.compare.3.label': 'Laser vs. Electrolysis',
 'laser.compare.3.text': 'Electrolysis treats one follicle at a time and is slow for large areas. Laser treats many follicles at once, far faster for legs, back, or full body.',
 'laser.compare.4.label': 'Single-wavelength vs. Triton',
 'laser.compare.4.text': 'Older lasers use one wavelength suited to limited skin types. Triton blends three wavelengths, so it is effective and safe across the full range of skin tones.',
 'laser.compare.5.label': 'Laser vs. Home devices',
 'laser.compare.5.text': 'Home IPL gadgets are low-powered and slow. A medical Triton laser, operated by a specialist, is far more effective and safer for all skin tones.',
 'laser.faq.1.q': 'Does laser hair removal hurt?',
 'laser.faq.1.a': 'Most people feel a quick warm snap with each pulse, but Triton’s built-in cooling keeps it very tolerable. Sensitive areas can feel a little more.',
 'laser.faq.2.q': 'How many sessions will I need?',
 'laser.faq.2.a': 'Typically 6–8 sessions spaced a few weeks apart, since laser works on hair in its active growth phase. Maintenance sessions keep results.',
 'laser.faq.3.q': 'Is it safe for dark or tanned skin?',
 'laser.faq.3.a': 'Yes — the Nd:YAG wavelength makes Triton safe and effective for darker and tanned skin, unlike older single-wavelength lasers.',
 'laser.faq.4.q': 'Is there downtime?',
 'laser.faq.4.a': 'No. Mild redness or warmth may appear briefly. You return to normal activities right away; avoid sun and heat for a day or two.',
 'laser.faq.5.q': 'Is it permanent?',
 'laser.faq.5.a': 'Laser gives long-lasting, permanent hair reduction. Most hair stops regrowing; occasional maintenance handles any hormone-driven regrowth.',
 'laser.faq.6.q': 'How should I prepare?',
 'laser.faq.6.a': 'Shave the area the day before, avoid sun, tanning, and waxing or plucking for a few weeks beforehand, and arrive with clean, product-free skin.',
 'laser.faq.7.q': 'Does it work on light or grey hair?',
 'laser.faq.7.a': 'Laser targets pigment, so very light, grey, white, or red hair responds poorly. A consultation will set the right expectation.',
 'laser.faq.8.q': 'Where can I have it done?',
 'laser.faq.8.a': 'Common areas include the upper lip, chin, underarms, arms, bikini line, legs, back, and full body. Your plan is tailored at consultation.',
 'laser.why.1': 'Authentic Triton by InMode — advanced three-wavelength laser',
 'laser.why.2': 'Safe and effective for all skin tones, including darker and tanned skin',
 'laser.why.3': 'Powerful built-in cooling for comfortable sessions',
 'laser.why.4': 'Performed by trained laser specialists after a skin assessment and patch test',
 'laser.why.5': 'Personalised settings for your skin tone, hair type, and area',
 'laser.why.6': 'Quick, efficient sessions with no downtime',
 'laser.why.7': 'Honest guidance on realistic results and the right number of sessions',
